Puerto Rico competed in the [[2009 World Baseball Classic]], hosting the games of Pool D at [[Estadio Hiram Bithorn]] in [[San Juan, Puerto Rico|San Juan]]. Puerto Rico secured advancement into Round 2 with wins over [[Panama national baseball team|Panama]] and the [[Netherlands national baseball team|Netherlands]], but were eliminated by the USA. For the first time ever in the [[2013 World Baseball Classic]] Puerto Rico has beaten [[Italy national baseball team|Italy]] and the USA, having lost in the first round, but won over the US team 4-3, and as well as winning against two-time defending champions [[Japan national baseball team|Japan]] in the first semifinal round, thus advancing them to the Finals, losing to the [[Dominican Republic national baseball team|Dominican Republic]] 3-0, finishing 2nd, which became a successful result from two previous [[World Baseball Classic]] games.

